2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the implementation of the SABM algorithm, which can be applied to improve network communication and data transmission. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The SABM algorithm involves marking bits in a product code, which can be seen as a data structure. The paper also discusses the implementation of the algorithm, which involves designing efficient algorithms. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The SABM algorithm can be applied to improve communication in social networks and other information networks. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the influence of suboptimal channel soft information on the SABM algorithm, which is a topic related to cryptography and security.
